name: Michael Schumacher
summary: Michael Schumacher's family is selling his personal watch collection, which includes pieces from some of his most iconic moments in Formula 1 racing. The collection, which is estimated to be worth over $6 million, will be auctioned off in November by Sotheby's in Geneva. Schumacher's wife, Corinna, said the decision to sell the watches was a difficult one, but they hope to use the proceeds to support charitable causes. The collection includes watches from Schumacher's last win in 2006, as well as from his record-breaking 1000th Formula 1 race in 2013. The sale of the watches comes as Schumacher continues to recover from a severe head injury he suffered while skiing in 2013.
